      "writtenOn": "2017-06-05T14:19:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s a detail of that implementation of the Gatherer interface. You could set it up so that the background go-routine is not started when the interval is 0 and use that feature in tests. It\u0027s not a big issue, but I don\u0027t think the Update method should be part of the Gatherer interface. It\u0027s more an implementation detail. A Gatherer should simply \"know\" what bots are down. I agreed that most often that will be through polling, but that\u0027s not necessarily always the case. \n\nAlternatively you could add a function to the gatherer package:\n\nfunc RepeatUpdate(g Gatherer, interval Duration) Gatherer { ....  }\n\nand then in main \n\ndownBots \u003d gatherer.RepeatUpdate(gatherer.New(....), *updatePeriod)\n\n...",
      "parentUuid": "85ed5a5e_d96f853b",
